### **5. COMPONENT REFACTORING RULES**

```typescript
// ✅ ALWAYS follow REFACTOR_COMPONENT_PROMPT.md when refactoring large components
// ✅ ALWAYS split files exceeding 200 lines
// ✅ ALWAYS organize into: components/, hooks/, services/, utils/, types/, store/
// ✅ ALWAYS preserve business logic exactly (NO changes to functionality)
// ✅ ALWAYS maintain same props interface and component name
// ✅ ALWAYS create index.ts files for clean imports

// ❌ NEVER modify business logic during refactoring
// ❌ NEVER change component behavior or UI appearance
// ❌ NEVER create files larger than 200 lines
// ❌ NEVER skip the organized folder structure
// ❌ NEVER refactor without following REFACTOR_COMPONENT_PROMPT.md
```

**REFERENCE:** `docs/important/prompts/CLEANcode/REFACTOR_COMPONENT_PROMPT.md`

**MANDATORY STRUCTURE:**
```
component-name/
├── page.tsx (or index.tsx)          # Main component entry point
├── components/                       # UI sub-components
│   ├── Component1.tsx
│   ├── Component2.tsx
│   └── index.ts
├── hooks/                           # Custom hooks
│   ├── useHook1.ts
│   ├── useHook2.ts
│   └── index.ts
├── services/                        # API calls and external services
│   └── api.ts
├── utils/                           # Helper functions and utilities
│   ├── helpers.ts
│   └── constants.ts
├── types/                           # TypeScript types and interfaces
│   └── types.ts
└── store/                           # State management (if applicable)
    └── store.ts
```

**FILE SIZE LIMIT:** Each file must NOT exceed 200 lines of code.

